Class LyricsFeatureExtractor

java.lang.Object
  jlyrics.features.LyricsFeatureExtractor
Direct Known Subclasses:
AutomatedReadabilityIndex, ContainsWords, LettersPerWordAverage, LettersPerWordVariance, LinesPerSegmentAverage, LinesPerSegmentVariance, NumberOfLines, NumberOfSegments, NumberOfUniqueWords, NumberOfWords, WordProfileMatch, WordsPerLineAverage, WordsPerLineVariance, WordVariety
public abstract class LyricsFeatureExtractor
extends java.lang.Object

The feature extractor prototype. Each class that extends this class will extract a particular feature from the lyrics of a song.

Classes that extend this class should have a constructor that sets the three protected fields of this class.

extractFeature

public abstract double[] extractFeature(SongLyrics lyrics,
                                        double[][] other_feature_values,
                                        java.lang.Object[][] external_information)
                                 throws java.lang.Exception
The prototype function that classes extending this class will override in order to extract their feature from song lyrics.

Parameters:
lyrics - The lyrics to extract the feature from.
other_feature_values - The values of other features that are needed to calculate this value. The order of these features must be the same as those returned by this class's getFeatureDepenedencies method. The first indice indicates the feature and the second indicates the value (in order to allow for multi-dimensional features).
external_information - Additional data of some kind that can be used to calculate a feature. The order of this data must be the same as that returned by this class's getExternalDependencies method. The first indice indicates the dependency and the second indicates the value.
Returns:
The extracted feature value. Null if the feature cannot be extracted from the given data.
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - Throws an informative exception if invalid data is provided.
